---
description: Remove redundant query/builder entry calls when equivalent direct APIs exist.
globs: **/*.php,**/*.js,**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Redundant Query Entrypoints

When a framework or library offers equivalent direct entrypoints, avoid redundant builder bootstrapping calls.

- Prefer the shortest equivalent query entrypoint.
- Keep explicit builder entry calls only when they are required for behavior.
- Preserve behavior; refactor style only when semantics stay the same.

```php
// Bad (redundant bootstrap)
$user = User::query()->where('email', $email)->first();

// Good (equivalent and clearer)
$user = User::where('email', $email)->first();
```

```ts
// Bad (redundant wrapper before filter)
const activeItems = data.getItems().query().where((item) => item.active);

// Good (equivalent direct pipeline)
const activeItems = data.getItems().where((item) => item.active);
```
